It seems like there is still an issue with generating a valid XML file.

Let me try to provide a more basic example that generates a single task in the XML format:
```python
import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET

# Create the root element
root = ET.Element("Task")

# Add driving point task
driving_point_task = ET.SubElement(root, "DrivingPoint")
ET.SubElement(driving_point_task, "description").text = "Drive to location"
ET.SubElement(driving_point_task, "reference").text = "https://www.geojson.org/properties.xml"

# Create the composite task information element
composite_task_info = ET.SubElement(root, "CompositeTaskInformation")

# Add driving point task if necessary
driving_point_task_if_condition = ET.SubElement(composite_task_info, "DrivingPoint")
ET.SubElement(driving_point_task_if_condition, "description").text = "Drive to location"
ET.SubElement(driving_point_task_if_condition, "reference").text = "https://www.geojson.org/properties.xml"

# Add IfCondition task if necessary
if_condition = ET.SubElement(composite_task_info, "IfCondition")
ET.SubElement(if_condition, "description").text = "Temperature is below 33 C"
ET.SubElement(if_condition, "conditionType").text = "Temperature"
ET.SubElement(if_condition, "operator").text = "LessThan"
ET.SubElement(if_condition, "value").text = str(33.0)

# Create the ElementTree object
tree = ET.ElementTree(root)

# Write the XML file
tree.write("output.xml", xml_declaration=True)
```
This should generate a valid XML file with no syntax errors.

Please note that this is just an example, and you will need to modify it to fit your specific requirements.